As the Universal Health Coverage (UHC) Forum convenes this week, coinciding with Universal Health Coverage Day, sub-Saharan Africa finds itself in the midst of a healthcare crisis. Toyin Saraki, founder-President of the Wellbeing Foundation Africa, who has been named as a UHC Global Champion at the forum in Tokyo, asks: Is universal health coverage the key to unlocking the potential of countries like Nigeria, to bring equality, health and wealth for all?